    • Method Detail

      • getByUniqueId

        java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<Profile> getByUniqueId(java.util.UUID uniqueId)
        Gets an CompletableFuture with the Profile of the player with the given unique identifier.

        If the cache does not contain the profile, the Future will throw a CompletionException caused by a NoSuchProfileException.

        Parameters:
        uniqueId - the unique identifier
        Returns:
        a Future with the corresponding Profile, if available

      • getByUniqueId

        java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<java.util.Set<Profile>> getByUniqueId(java.lang.Iterable<java.util.UUID> uniqueIds)
        Gets an CompletableFuture with a Set of Profiles of the players with the given unique identifiers, if available on this cache.

        If the cache does not contain a Profile for a given unique identifier, it will not be present in the returned Set. Alas, if none of the the given unique identifiers has a cached Profile, an empty Set will be returned.

        Parameters:
        uniqueIds - an Iterable of unique identifiers
        Returns:
        a Future with Set of corresponding Profiles, if available

      • getByName

        java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<Profile> getByName(java.lang.String name)
        Gets an CompletableFuture with the Profile of the player of the given name, if such a player exists.

        If the profile does not exist, the Future will throw a CompletionException caused by a NoSuchProfileException.

        This method may connect to a remote server in order to get the appropriate Profile.

        Parameters:
        name - the name
        Returns:
        a Future with the corresponding Profile, if available

      • getByName

        java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<java.util.Set<Profile>> getByName(java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String> names)
        Gets an CompletableFuture with a Set of Profiles of the players with the given unique identifiers, if available on this cache.

        If a Profile for a given name does not exist, it will not be present in the returned Set. Alas, if none of the the given names has a Profile, an empty Set will be returned.

        This method may connect to a remote server in order to get the appropriate Profile.

        Parameters:
        names - an Iterable of names
        Returns:
        a Future with a Set of corresponding Profiles
